This design system, which I've dubbed "Scharf Minimalist," is characterized by its high-contrast "split-screen" layout, heavy reliance on serif typography for editorial feel, and a monochromatic palette that uses subtle borders instead of shadows for depth.üé® Visual Analysis & TokensBased on the image provided, here are the core design tokens:TokenValueDescriptionPrimary Background#F4F4F4The soft grey main content area.Secondary Sidebar#0D0D0DThe deep black right-hand utility panel.Accent Border#D1D1D1Thin, 1px lines used for UI separation.Primary Text#1A1A1AHigh legibility near-black for body copy.Muted Text#666666Greyed out metadata (e.g., dates, author).Typography (Headings)Scharf / SerifLarge, airy leading with tracking adjustments.Typography (Body)Sans-SerifClean, functional font for UI and long-form.üõ†Ô∏è Implementation: tailwind.config.jsThis configuration captures the specific high-contrast layout and typography scales seen in the Art Basel article layout.JavaScriptmodule.exports = {
